\pard\nowidctlpar {{\cf0\f0 With the gest of the man who had said Ya Husayn, gradually, the strokes slackened. Plying the cymbal cut off. Now, only one person was taping on his drum. Mehran\uc0{\u8217}s brother. A lone brother who had a serious but sad face. The man who had said Ya Husayn shouted: \uc0{\u8220}Ya Ali\uc0{\u8221}. And the veins on his forehead and neck bulged. His face became blue. Mehran\uc0{\u8217}s brother left the drum and almost fainted. There was a dead silence. The silence whistling in my head, in my ears and my mind was still repeating the sound of drums and cymbals.}}\par
\pard\nowidctlpar {{\cf0\f0 Almost two months later, Mr Kamaly\uc0{\u8217}s daughter got married. Silently.}}\par
\pard\nowidctlpar {{\cf0\f0 To Mehran\uc0{\u8217}s brother. Serious but sad. Serious but happy.}}\par
